sover between short-range antiferromagnetic\nto ferromagnetic order in the intermediate temperature regime, a result broadly\nconsistent with the experimental findings. We find that this behavior is a\nfinite-temperature remnant of the underlying zero temperature phase transition,\nwhich we explore with ground state density matrix renormalization group\ncalculations. We provide evidence of ferromagnetism characterized by weak (but\nrobust) correlations that explain the small $\\Theta$ seen in the experiment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2022 18:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Jun 2023 03:02:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
